{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Continuous auto-deploy: the running Gerrit environment reflects `main` without manual deploy or restart\n\n## Why\nLanding a change on `main` does NOT update the running environment. The **review-bot container's\ncode**, the site `replication.config`, and the g2p config all require a MANUAL deploy (SSM /\nsetup-*.sh) and sometimes a restart, causing drift + toil: epic 88ab S2's merge-review code landed\non `main` but the running `compose-review-bot-1` still runs the pre-S2 image; the S3\n`replication.config` fix had to be hand-applied via SSM. The deployed environment must AUTO-REFLECT\n`main` shortly after a change lands, with no human on the box.\n\n## What\n### Trigger — RESOLVED: a systemd timer on the Gerrit host (option a; NOT GitHub Actions→SSM)\nA `rebar-autodeploy.timer` (every 2 min) runs `rebar-autodeploy.service` (a oneshot). RATIONALE for\nchoosing the on-box timer over a GitHub-Actions `deploy.yml` invoking SSM: (1) NO new trust surface\n— the box already has an instance role and reads the PUBLIC GitHub mirror READ-ONLY (no secret, no\nGitHub→AWS OIDC/`ssm:SendCommand` grant, which would make the GH runner a lateral-movement path into\nthe box); (2) self-contained + simplest to reason about + back out; (3) the ~2-min poll latency is\nacceptable for a deploy loop. Event-driven speed is not worth the added IAM/OIDC trust for this repo.\n\n### Deploy script (`infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh`, idempotent, flock-guarded)\n- **Concurrency guard:** `flock -n /var/lib/rebar/deploy.lock` — overlapping timer fires skip (a\n  long deploy is never re-entered).\n- **Deployed-SHA state:** `/var/lib/rebar/deployed-sha`. Lifecycle: on FIRST run (file absent) it is\n  INITIALIZED to the box's current running SHA (the checked-out HEAD) WITHOUT deploying (adopt\n  current state), then written atomically (`mv` a tmp file) only after a SUCCESSFUL deploy.\n- **Safety / what to deploy:** fetch `origin/main` from the mirror. The mirror's `main` only advances\n  via Gerrit SUBMIT (post two-vote gate), so its tip is Verified BY CONSTRUCTION — no separate\n  Verified re-query needed; the safety property is \"deploy only the mirror's `main` tip, never an\n  arbitrary ref\". Skip (no-op) when `origin/main == deployed-sha`.\n- **Change detection (per component, path-set driven):** `git diff --name-only deployed-sha..origin/main`\n  intersected with a component path manifest (a config constant, evolvable):\n  - review-bot: `src/rebar/**`, `infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot`, `pyproject.toml`,\n    `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`\n  - replication: `infra/gerrit/replication.config`\n  - g2p: `infra/gerrit/gerrit_to_platform.ini.template`, `infra/gerrit/materialize-g2p-config.sh`\n- **Per-component apply (only if that component changed):**\n  - review-bot changed → `docker tag` the current `compose-review-bot` image to `:prev` (rollback\n    handle), then `docker compose up -d --build review-bot`; HEALTH CHECK the receiver (`curl -fsS\n    http://localhost:<port>/health`, or the process/ready probe) with a **30s timeout**; on failure\n    → `docker tag :prev` back + `up -d` (rollback) + emit a deploy-error marker; do NOT advance\n    deployed-sha.\n  - replication changed → re-materialise `replication.config` into the site etc (autoReload=true →\n    no restart) + the g2p bind-mount copy.\n  - g2p changed → `materialize-g2p-config.sh` (refresh both copies).\n- **SCOPE BOUNDARY (v1):** auto-deploy covers the review-bot container + replication.config + g2p\n  config — the components that drift on ordinary `main` changes. `refs/meta/config` (project.config)\n  is DELIBERATELY OUT of v1: it is rare, security-sensitive, and needs a Gerrit ADMIN SSH key that is\n  an operator-workstation credential (setup-project.sh) not present on the box; the deploy DETECTS a\n  project.config change and emits a \"manual refs/meta/config apply needed\" signal (metric + log)\n  rather than attempting it. (A follow-up can add on-box admin-key handling.)\n- **Retry/backoff:** transient git-fetch / docker failures retried up to 3× with backoff; persistent\n  failure → deploy-error marker + leave prior state (fail-safe, never half-updated).\n- **Observability:** structured deploy log (from→to SHA + components deployed) + `rebar/host:deploy_errors`\n  (host-probe grep of a `AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` marker, mirroring voter_errors) + a CloudWatch alarm with\n  an SNS action.\n- **Back-out:** `systemctl disable --now rebar-autodeploy.timer` stops auto-deploy; the manual path\n  (compose-up.sh / setup-*.sh) is unchanged and still works.\n\n## Scope\nThe deploy orchestrator + the systemd timer/service + safety/observability/back-out on the existing\ncompose stack. Reuses the existing idempotent setup/materialise appliers. refs/meta/config auto-apply\nis explicitly deferred (detect + signal only). No change to gate semantics (S1/S2) or the\nfeature-branch flow (88ab).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A change landing on `main` (post-gate + replicated) causes the running environment to reflect\n      it with NO manual action, within ≤ 5 minutes (2-min poll + deploy); the actual latency is\n      recorded from a live run\n- [ ] Idempotent + change-detected: a second run with no `main` change is a no-op (deployed-sha ==\n      origin/main → exit 0, nothing rebuilt); a run after a relevant change re-applies ONLY the\n      changed component(s) — verified for review-bot code, replication.config, and g2p separately\n- [ ] review-bot rebuilt + restarted ONLY when its source-set changed since deployed-sha (a docs-only\n      `main` change does NOT rebuild it); AFTER a code change, the running bot reflects the new code\n      (proven end-to-end — e.g. a merge change gets the S2 merge-change tag from the auto-deployed bot)\n- [ ] Safety: only the mirror's `main` tip is ever deployed; a post-redeploy health check (30s\n      timeout) gates success; a failed review-bot deploy ROLLS BACK to the `:prev` image and does not\n      advance deployed-sha (rollback proven live)\n- [ ] Concurrency: overlapping timer fires are serialized by flock (a second fire during a deploy is\n      a no-op); deployed-sha is written atomically only on success\n- [ ] project.config (refs/meta/config) changes are DETECTED and signalled (metric + log), not\n      silently ignored and not attempted (documented out-of-v1 boundary)\n- [ ] Deploy log + `deploy_errors` metric + alarm applied; back-out (`disable` the timer) documented +\n      tested; manual deploy path still works\n- [ ] Live-verified end-to-end on the running box: a real `main` change auto-deploys within the window"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783075998977973001,"uuid":"ce692e0f-54c0-4a17-9141-311ad2ff260a"}